{0 Pirouette Compiler}

{1 Overview}

The Pirouette compiler implements higher-order typed functional choreographies,
allowing developers to write distributed protocols as single, unified programs
that are then compiled to individual endpoint implementations.

The compiler translates choreographies (global descriptions of multi-party protocols)
into executable code for each participant through a multi-stage pipeline:
parsing, type checking, endpoint projection, and code generation.

Pirouette supports multiple communication backends (HTTP, shared memory) and
generates standalone programs that preserve the protocol guarantees specified
in the choreography.

{1 HTTP Runtime Modules}
{3 Config_parser}
- {!Http_pirc.Config_parser} - Parse YAML configuration files mapping locations to HTTP addresses
{3 Send_receive}
- {!Http_pirc.Send_receive} - Send and receive messages between endpoints over HTTP

{1 Internal Compiler Libraries}

Core libraries used throughout the Pirouette compilation pipeline:
{3 {!Ast_core} - Core AST definitions}

Core abstract syntax tree structures:

- {!Ast_core.Choreo} - Choreography AST
- {!Ast_core.Local} - Local endpoint AST
- {!Ast_core.Net} - Network AST

{3 {!Ast_utils} - AST Utilities}

AST traversal and manipulation utilities:

- Functions for extracting locations
- AST transformation helpers
- Utility functions for AST analysis

{3 {!Parsing} - Lexer and Parser}

Lexer and parser implementation using Menhir:

- {!Parsing.Lexer} - Main Lexer
- {!Parsing.Net_lexer} - Network Lexer
- {!page-Net_parser} - Network Parser
- {!Parsing.Parse} - Parsing entry point 
- {!Parsing.Parsed_ast} - Parsed AST representation 
- {!page-Parser} - Main Parser

{3 {!Typing} - Type System}

Type checking and inference:

- Type rules for choreographies
- Location-aware types
- Type safety verification

{3 {!Netgen} - Code Generation}

Network code generation and endpoint projection:

- Projects choreographies onto endpoints
- Generates communication protocols
- Ensures protocol compliance

{3 {!Ocamlgen} - OCaml Backend}

OCaml backend code generation with multiple output targets:

- {!Ocamlgen.Emit_core} - Core emission logic
- {!Ocamlgen.Msg_intf} - Message interface definitions
- {!Ocamlgen.Toplevel_domain} - Domain-based backend
- {!Ocamlgen.Toplevel_http} - HTTP-based backend
- {!Ocamlgen.Toplevel_mpi} - MPI-based backend

